ENTRY       EC 2.1.1.230                Enzyme
NAME        23S rRNA (adenosine1067-2'-O)-methyltransferase;
            23S rRNA A1067 2'-methyltransferase;
            thiostrepton-resistance methylase;
            nosiheptide-resistance methyltransferase
CLASS       Transferases;
            Transferring one-carbon groups;
            Methyltransferases
SYSNAME     S-adenosyl-L-methionine:23S rRNA (adenosine1067-2'-O)-methyltransferase
REACTION    S-adenosyl-L-methionine + adenosine1067 in 23S rRNA = S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + 2'-O-methyladenosine1067 in 23S rRNA
SUBSTRATE   S-adenosyl-L-methionine [CPD:C00019];
            adenosine1067 in 23S rRNA
PRODUCT     S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine [CPD:C00021];
            2'-O-methyladenosine1067 in 23S rRNA
COMMENT     The methylase that is responsible for autoimmunity in the thiostrepton producer Streptomyces azureus, renders ribosomes completely resistant to thiostrepton [2].
